SUMMARY:Really Free Market at Albina Library
DESCRIPTION:Albina Library\, Community Room A \nBring what you can\, take what you need. The perfect opportunity for little ones to swap toys and for adults to get some new stuff too! \nItems must be clean\, useful\, and library appropriate. \nIf you choose to bring items (not required)\, you must take all leftover items home with you. This is not sponsored by a charity\, it’s not a donation drop-off\, this is a community based event organized by a couple of local Portlanders. \nNo money\, no trade\, everything is free! \nEditor’s note: This event is a community submission.
URL:https://pdxparent.com/event-single/really-free-market-at-albina-library/
LOCATION:Albina Library\, 205 NE Russell St\, Portland\, OR\, 97212\, United States
CATEGORIES:Books/Library,Indoor,Kids Calendar
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://pdxparent.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_3353.jpeg
ORGANIZER;CN="Casper &amp%3B Sean Menson":MAILTO:csmenson@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
